Main article: Indo-Pakistani War of 1965Main article: Indo-Pakistani War of 1971In 1965 and 1971, heavy fighting again broke out between India and Pakistan.
The Indo-Pakistani War of 1971 resulted in the defeat of Pakistan and Pakistan Military's surrender in East Pakistan (Bangladesh).
At the same time, fears of the Kargil War turning into a nuclear war, provoked the then-US President Bill Clinton to pressure Pakistan to retreat.
